``dature`` CLI now parses its own arguments through ``ArgparseSource``: the schema it loads into is built at runtime from the signature of ``load()`` via ``dataclasses.make_dataclass``, so CLI flags stay in sync with the public API automatically. ``main()`` no longer accepts an ``argv`` parameter — like ``ArgparseSource`` itself, it reads ``sys.argv`` directly. Bool actions registered with ``default=None`` are now suppressed from ``ArgparseSource`` output (treated as "unset", same as non-bool flags), so absence on the CLI falls back to the schema/dataclass default rather than emitting a literal ``None``.
